        <heading>954.  Traffic violations adjudicated on citation; petition not required</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 954.  Traffic violations adjudicated on citation; petition not required
In cases of traffic violations, a petition is not required.  The child may be summoned to appear and the case may be instituted with a uniform traffic citation.  The citation shall describe in general terms the nature of the violation.  The citation or summons may direct the child to bring a parent with him when he appears.</p>
        </content>
